<p class=3D"rubric">Notes</p>
<p>For non-sparse models, i.e. when there are not many zeros in <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">coef_</span></code>,
this may actually <em>increase</em> memory usage, so use this method with
care. A rule of thumb is that the number of zero elements, which can
be computed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">(coef_</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre=
">0).sum()</span></code>, must be more than 50% for this
to provide significant benefits.</p>
<p>After calling this method, further fitting with the partial_fit
